Vice-President Yemi Osinbajo has paid a condolence visit to Nasarawa over the recent deaths in the state. At least 37 persons were reported dead following an airstrike in Kwateri, a community between Benue and Nasarawa states, on Tuesday. Also,Â TheCable had reported that Hassan, the 36-year-old son of Abdullahi Sule, governor of Nasarawa, died on Thursday. Osinbajo prayed for God to comfort the governor and his family, just as he also commiserated with the families of those who died in the Tuesday incident. The vice-president shared photos of the visit on his social media pages. See photos below.          